FBIS3-57882 "drweu003_o_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 CYPRUS Spokesman Calls Turkish Reports on Shooting Unfounded NC0401123894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1130 GMT 4 Jan 94 NC0401123894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis rejected as entirely unfounded Turkish allegations that shots were fired on the confrontation line. Mr. Kasoulidhis said that these allegations, which have not been confirmed by the UNFICYP [UN Forces in Cyprus], are aimed at creating tension and are not irrelevant with statements by Turkish officials against Greece on allegedly intransigent positions.
